-- Egypt Allocates Additional $100 Million for Fuel Purchases
-- B y   A b d e l   L a t i f   W a h b a
-- 2012-07-22T14:33:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/egypt-allocates-additional-100-million-for-fuel-purchases.html
Egypt’s  Finance Ministry  said it
allocated an additional $100 million for fuel purchases to
ensure adequate supplies in the market and took “urgent
measures” to ensure that other commodities are available.  The additional funds increased to $6.1 billion the amount
given to the Egyptian General Petroleum Corp., Finance Minister
Momtaz el-Saieed said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Abdel Latif Wahba in Cairo at 
 alatifwahba@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden in Dubai at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  